TEXT(beginproblem());

############################################################
# PG Setup Code
############################################################
Context("Numeric");
$f = Formula("sqrt(x)");
Context("Interval");
$domain = Interval("(-inf,inf)");
Context("Interval");
$range = Interval("(-inf,5)");
Context("Point");
$intercept = Point("(0,4)");
Context("LimitedNumeric");
$ha = Real(5);

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
The graph of an exponential function is given above. Answer the following questions about that graph.
a.  What is the domain of the function, in interval notation? [_]{$domain}{10}.

a.  What is the range of the function, in interval notation? [_]{$range}{10}.

a.  What is the [`y`]-intercept of the function? [_]{$intercept}{10}. (Enter your answer in point form, for example [`(3,5)\text{.}`])

a.  What is the equation of the horizontal asymptote? The horizontal asymptote is [`y=`] [_]{$ha}{10}. (Enter a single number.)

END_PGML

############################################################
# End Problem
